BlackAndLoki
collywollyAnother question: I have a dino at level 39 with the option to choose reincarnation. Should I go for it? What, exactly, happens and how can I make the best use of this skill?

It depends, if your dinoz perfect no need to reincarnate it. Reincarnation will set your dinoz to level 1 and will give you 5 additional element rolsl distributed randomly but due to probabilities of rolls.
Of course if you rise a reincarnated dinoz and get good rolls your dinoz will be stronger as the same not reincarnated simple cause it will have 5 more elements (but important actually only the additional rolls in main elements). Reincarnation also allows to redo all missions (get secodn sphere with this dnoz). You can reincarnate dinoz only once and the problem is when you screw reincarnated dinoz due to bad luck with rolls it is not nice. Cause you loose Demon Notes that you could get for the dinoz simple sacrificing him instead of reincarnating. When you already have strong team you can start reincarnate some dinoz in order to get even stronger fighters. Or if you for some reason like the look of your dinoz so much that you want to keep him and if it got the bad rolls you can reincarnate him and try again.

If you see you roll wood to much drop tenacity go for Wild instinct if you have enough air to aim for ET also or simple for acrobat if you forced in wood. The "training center" (forgot its real name) is definitely NOT worth it.
Just stay in the dark world and grind until lvl 29.

Superdome: If you got a good pvp team its nice to make some money for a few fights, until you place higher in the ranking and have tougher fights. So if you are in to good pvp fights, thats the main reason for the super dome later on. You dont need to have godly dinoz...
A team of 5 lvl 30 dinoz might even be enough to defeat 2 or 3 or 4 opponents, especially if their team is smaller (Team of 3 for example). Anyways, eventually you´ll face strong opponents so i´d rather keep on levelling.

Bruteforce:
Its very good to get some additional xp if you miss some for a level up. Also good during waiting times in events, when you hang around in dtown with close to no xp. Use it if you miss some important skills or want/need to have a quick level up.
Example: you are done with the dark world...lvl 29. Do some easy xp missions...lvl 30. You still lack some good A skills or key skills like sumo, that would decrease your taken damage in Nimbao by 50-100%.... Do some bruteforce fights.
Back in the days, it was the #1 method, combined with venerable, to make some xp while beeing lvl 49, since xp in nimbao drops rapidly then. But now, this is obsolote...so use it whenever you think it might be worth the 1-irma vs 30+x xp ratio

I Hope that helps

Of course it's hard to achieve this, as you can't predict your rolls exactly, but with the level cap raised it's already proven to be possible. I put all double skills in air level ups, but that can of course be changed to the other elements as well.

If you don't hit enough fire (or more than enough) -> take warm blood
In wood -> just stick to the plan, tenacity is not a serious alternative. If you're REALLY low on wood levels, like first wood level around lvl20, I'd go for endurance and growth and also skip Tai Chi (and Ejector Palms) in air.
More water? -> perception, kaar-sher beam, without mercy are nice.
Way less water? -> no underwater karate, or in later stage no poisoned claws/acid blood.
Air shouldn't be a big problem, if you don't hit enough of it, consider dropping vacuum disk and black hole.
If you don't hit enough lightning, skip lightning attack and hazard.

For a basic build (without TM(!)):
Don't go for earth tremor, but go for carapace and vines (and primal state if you hit more).
In fire go for warm blood, if you keep hitting fire, try to reach self-control.
Also skip Achilles Heel, Tai Chi and Ejector Palms in air.

Go to The Tunnel Under the Branch
Go to Lava Pit
Go to Dinotown
Defeat 3 Korgon Avengers (maybe you just have to use the option fight there if you already passed all the previous locations)
Go to Waikiki Island
Go to Sticky Swamp
Defeat 2 Korgon Avengers
This Korgon will have the Cursed Wand. If you do not kill it immediately, you will become cursed. This curse will stop your dinoz from getting any XP. The cure is at the Cursed shop at the Ashpouk ruins. Only cursed dinoz can see this shop. Stock up on Devils Ointment while you're there, because this costs a lot of XP otherwise!

If you do this mission with 3 dinoz you will have to fight 3 times (1 for each dino) so I advise you when you do one fight to make a leader of the group the second dino that needs to kill this korgons before to click the option and then for the 3-rd dino to do the same because if the dinoz that has to fight the korgons are not leader they will fight alone, but if they are leader of the group they will fight with the other 2. Be sure you have turn available for the whole 3 dinoz before to fight also

Go to Lavapit and validate the mission.

more on sphere skills

The best "overall" spheres depends on dinoz type actually. But there are some spherical skilsl that are good fro any type of the dinoz. Like 1 lightning sphere gives you Reflex (+5 ini) it is good for all dinoz, but heavy lightning dinoz (Rocky, wans, glids, sometimes winks and cloudoz) also need the second sphere to get a strong Sinous Lightning skill. Also brave low ini pigs when grinding in caushemesh need 3 lightning spheres to get Survival if you don't ahve enough napos for Cursed Locker.

3 Air spheres are good fro all cause 2 of them give you Smelly Aura and 3 gives you Hypnosis both first is a god skil for Dojoquali and without items dojo and second is good for MWs and COTC.

2 Water sphere are good for almost all dinoz they give Vitality and Stumbs. The third spehre is great fro heavy water dinoz casue it gives very powerful A-skill that also reduce Endurance of the enemy.

1 wood sphere is good for wood heavy wans, mahamutis and for gorilloz. A specialist or overload specialist dinoz can make a good use of 3 wood spheres casue of good whack.

1 Fire spheres is good for heavy fire dinoz like pigs and mouffes.

But you should give spheres only to dinoz starting from lvl 40-45, when you see that your dinoz will most probably turn out good.

On april 25, 2013
Loppermann
rrudnicI just finished up the missions from the Elemental Master and I am not sure what to do now. I have walked all around looking for new missions. What comes after the EM?

Firstly, if you haven't already, talk to the EM with the dinoz that has finished those missions and follow the dialogue to get a sphere (they can be quite valuable). Then you can go to the Forest (via the Deep Gorges) and do Diana's missions. Doing the first one will give you access to the whole forest. You need to have the lantern to get past the Tunnel Under the Branch, so you can only do this with your softpig so far.

After you have access to the whole forest, you can do the Forest Warden missions at the Blacksylva Door. Once you have 7 dinoz that have done Diane's first mission, you can focus at Bao Bob's place with them (you can also do this with other members of your clan, but since you're the only one in your clan that won't be of use to you).

Well, that information should keep you busy for a few months
Most of the top clans have this kind of information in their public clan pages if you want more in-depth information.
